reviewText:
Pros: Nice atmosphere and theme;
Cons: creates the false appearance of deep strategic choice where none exists
Cons: Infuriating RNG and Luck based game - totally at the mercy of random luck and with limited options to mitigate against it;
Cons: Difficulty is artificially high due to RNG and Luck based systems that go too far and take all of the strategy and fun out of the game
Cons: game incomplete. Missions (campaign) missing from the game; states this feature is coming soon whatever that means
Cons: low replayability and high frustration factor
Cons: Game is too costly for what it is: a gloried browser game with nicer graphics. Not worth more than $5 at most;
Cons: You will likely quit in frustration within a few hours.
Cons: No undo move if you make any error.
Conclusion:  I was hoping this game was going to be something special. It turned out to be a big disappointment at least for me. I wish the devs take these conplaints to heart and fix the issues that are holding the game back.
